🏦 Banking System Backend
📖 About The Project
A simplified banking backend system built with Python and SQLite that simulates real banking operations such as account management, deposits, withdrawals, transaction tracking, and ledger accounting. This project demonstrates backend development fundamentals, including database design, transaction processing, SQL querying, and AI-powered anomaly detection.

🎯 Learning Objectives
Master database design and SQL fundamentals

Implement transaction processing with rollback support

Build AI-powered anomaly detection systems

Practice data integrity testing with SQL

Understand financial ledger systems

Develop CLI-based applications

🏗️ Project Architecture
text
banking-ledger-system/
├── python/                  # Backend application layer
├── sql/                     # Database schema and queries
├── tests/                   # Comprehensive SQL test suite
└── bank.db                  # SQLite database
🛠️ Tech Stack
Python 3.13 - Backend application logic

SQLite - Lightweight relational database

Pandas & NumPy - Statistical analysis

Scikit-learn - AI/ML anomaly detection

Unittest - Python testing framework

SQL - Data querying and reporting

